---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Accessibility Statement | North Country Realty Group">
  <Header />
  
  <main id="main-content">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-navy-dark py-16 relative">
      <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gold"></div>
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center">
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl text-white mb-4">
          Accessibility Statement
        </h1>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <article class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl">
        <div class="prose prose-lg">
          
          <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy-dark mb-4">Our Commitment</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              North Country Realty Group is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We strive to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, Level AA standards. These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible for people with disabilities and more user-friendly for everyone.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Our website has achieved a <strong class="text-navy-dark">10/10 WAVE accessibility score</strong>, demonstrating our dedication to providing an inclusive experience for all users, including those who rely on assistive technologies.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy-dark mb-4">What We've Done</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We have implemented the following accessibility features throughout our website:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Semantic HTML:</strong> Proper use of headings, landmarks, lists, and other structural elements to ensure logical content organization</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Keyboard Navigation:</strong> All interactive elements are fully accessible via keyboard, with visible focus indicators</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Screen Reader Support:</strong> ARIA labels, roles, and live regions where appropriate to enhance the experience for screen reader users</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Color Contrast:</strong> Text and interactive elements meet WCAG AA contrast requirements (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Alternative Text:</strong> Descriptive alt text for all meaningful images; decorative images are marked appropriately</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Skip Links:</strong> A "Skip to main content" link is provided to bypass repetitive navigation</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Form Labels:</strong> All form inputs have visible, associated labels and clear error messaging</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Responsive Design:</strong> Content is accessible and functional across all device sizes and orientations</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy-dark mb-4">Known Limitations</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              While we strive for full accessibility, some limitations exist:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Placeholder Images:</strong> Demo property listings currently use placeholder images. These will be replaced with actual property photos with descriptive alt text as listings are added.</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Third-Party Content:</strong> Some embedded content from third-party services (such as maps) may not fully meet accessibility standards.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              We are actively working to address these limitations and improve accessibility across all areas of our website.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy-dark mb-4">Feedback</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website. If you encounter any accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please contact us:
            </p>
            <address class="not-italic text-gray-700 mb-4">
              <p class="mb-2">
                <strong class="text-navy-dark">Email:</strong> 
                <a href="mailto:info@northcountryrealty.com" class="text-gold hover:text-gold-dark underline transition-colors focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-gold focus-visible:ring-offset-2 rounded">
                  info@northcountryrealty.com
                </a>
              </p>
              <p class="mb-2"><strong class="text-navy-dark">Phone:</strong> (603) 555-0123</p>
              <p><strong class="text-navy-dark">Address:</strong> 123 Main Street, Lancaster, NH 03584</p>
            </address>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              We try to respond to accessibility feedback within 2 business days and will work with you to resolve any issues.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy-dark mb-4">Technical Specifications</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              This website has been built using the following technologies and standards:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Framework:</strong> Astro with Tailwind CSS v4</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Accessibility Standard:</strong> WCAG 2.1 Level AA</li>
              <li><strong class="text-navy-dark">Testing Tools:</strong> WAVE Web Accessibility Evaluation Tool, axe DevTools, manual keyboard and screen reader testing</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4 mb-2">
              <strong class="text-navy-dark">Supported Browsers:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-1 ml-4">
              <li>Google Chrome (latest 2 versions)</li>
              <li>Mozilla Firefox (latest 2 versions)</li>
              <li>Apple Safari (latest 2 versions)</li>
              <li>Microsoft Edge (latest 2 versions)</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
            <a 
              href="/" 
              class="inline-flex items-center text-gold hover:text-gold-dark transition-colors focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-gold focus-visible:ring-offset-2 rounded"
            >
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"></path>
              </svg>
              Back to Home
            </a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
